narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A fascinating, low-pressure course; something that is really refreshing to take on the side of harder, more time-consuming classes. Expect about three or four hours of homework a week - easily doable.
I would recommend the class to another student interested in music, even someone who has just played an instrument in the past.

I expected this to be an easy course just cause I've been playing an instrument for 15 years but that didn't help at all. It was a bunch of work to have assignments due every class and quizzes, but we did learn all the material well. Tahirih was great. Rondo Alla turca starts with a B section and nobody will convince me otherwise.
